Events.RelatedDescription: Opened issue "Image not shown correctly after removing some other images from Table via removal of Rows" (#935) at OfficeDev/Open-XML-SDK
Events.RelatedBody:
This issue is a:
- [x] Issue with the OpenXml library
- [ ] Question on library usage

**Description**

Related stackoverflow question: [here](https://stackoverflow.com/questions/67313699/open-xml-removal-of-ms-word-table-rows-corrupting-images). However when the process document is uploaded to SharePoint and if viewed in "Edit" mode the images are shown correctly but view mode again corrupts the images inside the table.

Opened issue "Incorrect nullability annotations for OpenXmlComparableSimpleReference operator ==/!=" (#933) at OfficeDev/Open-XML-SDK
Events.RelatedBody:
**Description**

https://github.com/OfficeDev/Open-XML-SDK/blob/main/src/DocumentFormat.OpenXml/SimpleTypes/OpenXmlComparableSimpleReference.cs#L131
https://github.com/OfficeDev/Open-XML-SDK/blob/main/src/DocumentFormat.OpenXml/SimpleTypes/OpenXmlComparableSimpleReference.cs#L147

Operators parameters not marked as nullable which leads to following error when checking derived instances (e.g. StringValue) for null.

**Information**

- .NET Target: net48, net5.0
- DocumentFormat.OpenXml Version: 2.13.0

**Repro**

```cs
// CS8604	Possible null reference argument for parameter 'left' in 'bool OpenXmlComparableSimpleReference<string>.operator !=(OpenXmlComparableSimpleReference<string> left, OpenXmlComparableSimpleReference<string> right)'.
if (cell.CellReference != null)
```

**Observed**

error generated

**Expected**

no error generated

Events.RelatedDescription: Closed issue "New NuGet prerelease 2.13.0-beta0002 with Office 2019 support" (#922) at OfficeDev/Open-XML-SDK
Events.RelatedBody:
This is a note that on April 20th we released Beta 2 version of SDK with support for Office 2019: namespaces and generated classes. Please give it a try and report issues, specifying NuGet package version number.

You need to check “Include prerelease” in VS NuGet Package Manager to see 2.13.0-beta0002 version.
